TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,8,1);
$b = random(3,7,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find the antiderivatives for
$BR
\[
\frac{dx}{dt} = $a t^{-1} + $b.
\]
$BR
\(x = \) \{ans_rule(35) \} + \( C\).
$BR
$BR
Hint: In WeBWorK, you write \(|x|\) with "abs(x)".
$BR

EOT

$ans = "$a*ln(abs(t)) + $b*t";
&ANS(function_cmp_up_to_constant($ans,"t"));

ENDDOCUMENT();
